thread.title: Bilinski leads NorthWood upset

title: Bilinski leads NorthWood upset
text:
Bilinski leads NorthWood upset 
Trey Bilinski threw three touchdown passes and Tanner Cleveland completed his only pass with what proved to be the game-winner in the fourth quarter as unranked NorthWood upset No. 7-ranked Plymouth, 33-30, in high school football Friday night. 
Plymouth (7-2, 5-2 NLC) took a 15-6 lead in the second quarter before the 6-3 (4-3) Panthers ran off 27 straight points as Bilinski completed TD throws of 5 and 75 yards to Bronson Yoder and 18 yards to Drew Minnich. Cleveland then hit Stump on a 6-yard score for a 33-15 lead before the Rockies tried to rally. Subscription Required An online service is needed to view this article in its entirety.
